00:33:52.869 --> 00:33:54.106
Wait.

511
00:34:00.008 --> 00:34:01.773
Come on!

512
00:34:12.185 --> 00:34:13.389
Come on!

513
00:34:16.923 --> 00:34:19.362
Come on!
This ship is going to explode!

514
00:34:21.065 --> 00:34:22.866
What are you doing?

515
00:34:23.002 --> 00:34:25.300
Find me when you wake up.

516
00:34:25.436 --> 00:34:27.198
- What?!
- Come find me when you wake up.

517
00:34:31.372 --> 00:34:33.673
On your feet. maggot!

518
00:34:37.078 --> 00:34:39.979
Get in line before I bust your
hole with my boot heel. maggot!

519
00:34:40.115 --> 00:34:41.820
Good news is there's hope
for you. private.

520
00:34:41.956 --> 00:34:43.487
Battle is the great redeemer.

521
00:34:43.622 --> 00:34:46.654
The fiery crucible in which
the only true heroes are forged.

522
00:34:46.789 --> 00:34:49.359
The one place where all men
truly sh-share the..

523
00:34:55.398 --> 00:34:56.463
Squad. this here
is Private Cage.

524
00:34:56.598 --> 00:34:58.632
Private Cage.
And you must be J squad.

525
00:34:59.972 --> 00:35:01.103
It's good to meet you.

526
00:35:01.238 --> 00:35:02.800
Isn't that an officer's uniform?

527
00:35:02.936 --> 00:35:05.309
These sure ain't
officer's cuff links.

528
00:35:08.246 --> 00:35:11.777
Keys in the left
pocket probably.

529
00:35:16.253 --> 00:35:18.850
Private Cage is a deserter.

530
00:35:18.985 --> 00:35:20.923
I'm making you all
personally responsible

531
00:35:21.058 --> 00:35:22.590
for his deliverance.

532
00:35:22.725 --> 00:35:26.494
He will be combat-ready
by 0600 tomorrow.

533
00:35:26.629 --> 00:35:27.656
'Private Cage is
under the delusion'

534
00:35:27.792 --> 00:35:29.091
'he does not belong here.'

535
00:35:29.226 --> 00:35:30.995
'We must dissuade him
of this delusion.'

536
00:35:31.130 --> 00:35:32.862
- If he tries to run. free--
- Oh. no. no. no.

537
00:35:32.997 --> 00:35:34.739
I'm-I'm not going to run
from you guys.

538
00:35:34.875 --> 00:35:36.139
It's. uh. not a chance.

539
00:35:36.274 --> 00:35:37.699
Till he can't piss standin' up.

540
00:35:37.835 --> 00:35:39.508
Thank you. Sergeant Farell.

541
00:35:51.949 --> 00:35:54.817
What next?
A little. uh. P.T.?

542
00:35:54.953 --> 00:35:56.824
'P.T.! Ten minutes!'

543
00:35:56.960 --> 00:35:58.497
'Left!'

544
00:35:58.632 --> 00:35:59.696
Left!

545
00:35:59.831 --> 00:36:00.765
Left!

546
00:36:00.901 --> 00:36:02.493
What are you? Sound off!

547
00:36:02.628 --> 00:36:04.069
'I'm a warrior!'

548
00:36:04.204 --> 00:36:06.137
- What do warriors do?
- Kill!

549
00:36:06.273 --> 00:36:07.898
- 'What are you gonna do?'
- Kill!

550
00:36:08.034 --> 00:36:09.739
- 'What are you gonna do?!'
- 'Kill!'

551
00:36:09.875 --> 00:36:12.043
'It's gonna be my
20th battle tomorrow. man.'

552
00:36:12.179 --> 00:36:13.337
You haven't been
in 20 battles. mate.

553
00:36:13.472 --> 00:36:14.541
I have to.

554
00:36:14.676 --> 00:36:15.572
You're gonna dump
your load the second

555
00:36:15.708 --> 00:36:17.173
we hit the beach tomorrow.

556
00:36:17.308 --> 00:36:18.981
Why don't you two get
yourselves a nice hot cup

557
00:36:19.117 --> 00:36:20.147
of shut-the-hell-up!

558
00:36:20.283 --> 00:36:21.749
Ha-ha. You funny. girl.

559
00:36:21.885 --> 00:36:23.747
But I bet you I set some kind
of record tomorrow.

560
00:36:23.883 --> 00:36:25.681
Fastest time runnin'
backwards. Ford.

561
00:36:25.816 --> 00:36:26.714
Slippin' in your own shit.

562
00:36:26.850 --> 00:36:28.057
Kill!

563
00:36:28.193 --> 00:36:30.821
Knock off the grab-ass!

564
00:36:30.956 --> 00:36:33.265
- Grab this. sarge!
- Hold up!

565
00:36:36.036 --> 00:36:38.127
Private. drop and give me..

566
00:36:40.038 --> 00:36:42.300
Fifty. sarge?

567
00:36:42.436 --> 00:36:43.905
That's right.

568
00:36:44.040 --> 00:36:46.104
Fifty.

569
00:36:46.240 --> 00:36:47.306
Platoon!

570
00:36:47.442 --> 00:36:49.244
Drop and give me fifty!

571
00:36:49.379 --> 00:36:51.544
Compliments of Private Cage.

572
00:36:51.679 --> 00:36:53.082
'Thank you. sarge!'

573
00:36:53.218 --> 00:36:54.248
- And one!
- One!

574
00:36:54.384 --> 00:36:56.119
- 'And two!'
- Two!

575
00:36:56.255 --> 00:36:57.787
- 'And three!'
- Three!

576
00:36:57.922 --> 00:36:59.790
Four!

577
00:36:59.925 --> 00:37:02.154
Five! Six!

578
00:37:02.289 --> 00:37:03.761
Seven!

579
00:37:08.401 --> 00:37:10.135
What the hell
were you thinkin'?

580
00:37:10.271 --> 00:37:11.863
'There's hope for you. private.'

581
00:37:11.998 --> 00:37:14.236
Hope in the form
of glorious combat.

582
00:37:14.372 --> 00:37:16.104
Battle is the great redeemer..

583
00:37:16.239 --> 00:37:17.204
Two!

584
00:37:17.339 --> 00:37:18.601
- Three!
- Three!

585
00:37:18.736 --> 00:37:20.240
- Four!
- Four!

586
00:37:20.375 --> 00:37:22.437
- Five!
- Five!

587
00:37:22.573 --> 00:37:23.747
Six!

588
00:37:23.882 --> 00:37:24.913
Seven!

589
00:37:25.048 --> 00:37:26.410
Eight!

590
00:37:26.545 --> 00:37:28.720
Nine! Ten!

591
00:37:28.855 --> 00:37:31.418
Eleven! Twelve!

592
00:37:31.553 --> 00:37:32.885
Thirteen!
Fourteen!

593
00:38:05.182 --> 00:38:07.524
Excuse me.
Sergeant Vrataski.

594
00:38:10.831 --> 00:38:11.957
Excuse me!

595
00:38:13.263 --> 00:38:14.531
Sergeant Vrataski?

596
00:38:34.682 --> 00:38:36.010
- Excuse me!
- Yes?

597
00:38:36.146 --> 00:38:38.852
Who said you could talk to me?

598
00:38:38.987 --> 00:38:41.221
Have I got something
on my face. soldier?

599
00:38:41.356 --> 00:38:42.586
You did. you did

600
00:38:42.721 --> 00:38:44.655
tomorrow at the beach.

601
00:38:44.790 --> 00:38:46.563
Tomorrow at the beach.

602
00:38:48.461 --> 00:38:49.926
We meet.

603
00:38:50.062 --> 00:38:52.833
You said to find you
when I wake up.

604
00:38:55.837 --> 00:38:58.008
You do know
what's happening to me.

605
00:38:58.143 --> 00:39:01.510
Come with me. Now.

606
00:39:01.646 --> 00:39:04.346
You don't talk to anyone
about this but me.

607
00:39:04.481 --> 00:39:05.712
'Cause the
best case scenario

608
00:39:05.847 --> 00:39:08.046
is you're gonna end up
in a psych ward.

609
00:39:08.181 --> 00:39:09.913
And the worst case. you'll get
dissected for study.

610
00:39:10.048 --> 00:39:12.388
- Are we clear? Yes?
- Yes.

611
00:39:12.523 --> 00:39:14.357
First time you died.
what happened?

612
00:39:14.493 --> 00:39:16.052
- You killed a mimic?
- Yes.

613
00:39:16.187 --> 00:39:18.526
- Describe it.
- Um. it was different.

614
00:39:18.662 --> 00:39:21.859
It was. uh. bigger.
Bluish.

615
00:39:21.994 --> 00:39:24.531
And you got covered
in its blood.

616
00:39:24.666 --> 00:39:26.833
As a matter of fact. I did.

617
00:39:26.968 --> 00:39:29.667
They know we're coming
on the beach tomorrow.

618
00:39:29.803 --> 00:39:32.340
It's a slaughter. isn't it?

619
00:39:32.475 --> 00:39:34.006
How do you know this?

620
00:39:35.313 --> 00:39:36.748
Could you just.. Wait!

621
00:39:36.884 --> 00:39:38.943
Wait. Wait.

622
00:39:39.079 --> 00:39:40.942
Look. would you please
just explain to me

623
00:39:41.078 --> 00:39:42.385
what the hell is happening?

624
00:39:42.521 --> 00:39:44.715
What happened to you
happened to me.

625
00:39:44.851 --> 00:39:47.458
I had it. I lost it.
Okay?

626
00:39:47.594 --> 00:39:48.818
I mean. that's great.
There's a cure.

627
00:39:48.954 --> 00:39:49.917
How do I get rid of this?

628
00:39:50.053 --> 00:39:51.623
First. I need your help.

629
00:39:51.759 --> 00:39:54.756
Help with-with what exactly?

630
00:39:54.891 --> 00:39:56.759
Winning the war.

631
00:39:56.895 --> 00:39:58.166
'Let's go! Come on!'

632
00:40:36.403 --> 00:40:38.441
Rita. what is this?
Rita. what are you doing here?

633
00:40:38.576 --> 00:40:39.767
You gotta give me
some warning.

634
00:40:39.903 --> 00:40:41.002
Who's this?

635
00:40:41.137 --> 00:40:43.311
He's me before Verdun.

636
00:40:43.447 --> 00:40:44.780
He's gonna help us.

637
00:40:49.180 --> 00:40:50.953
What?
You-you mean he's--

638
00:40:51.088 --> 00:40:52.557
Yes.

639
00:40:54.821 --> 00:40:55.785
When did he die? Where?

640
00:40:55.921 --> 00:40:57.496
On the beach. Tomorrow.

641
00:40:59.689 --> 00:41:01.956
How many fingers am I
holding up behind my back?

642
00:41:02.092 --> 00:41:04.628
How should I know that?

643
00:41:04.763 --> 00:41:07.464
Okay. so..

644
00:41:07.600 --> 00:41:09.130
...this is the first time
we've had this conversation.

645
00:41:09.265 --> 00:41:11.134
You should try this on him.

646
00:41:11.270 --> 00:41:13.710
- What the hell is that?
- It doesn't work.

647
00:41:15.441 --> 00:41:17.141
- Has he had any visions yet?
- Visions of what?

648
00:41:17.276 --> 00:41:18.613
- Okay. so there's still time.
- Yes.

649
00:41:18.749 --> 00:41:20.314
Time? Look.
I-I'm sorry. Which is..

650
00:41:20.449 --> 00:41:21.612
Who is this?

651
00:41:21.747 --> 00:41:23.218
Who are you?

652
00:41:23.353 --> 00:41:24.655
I'm Dr. Carter.

653
00:41:24.790 --> 00:41:26.889
Particle physics.
Advanced microbiology.

654
00:41:27.024 --> 00:41:28.351
'He's also
the only other person'

655
00:41:28.486 --> 00:41:30.188
'who'll believe
what's happening to you.'

656
00:41:30.323 --> 00:41:32.991
No one understands mimic
biology better than him.

657
00:41:33.127 --> 00:41:35.128
He's a top analyst
at Whitehall.

658
00:41:35.263 --> 00:41:38.062
Well. I mean. I was until
I met Rita and now I'm just a

659
00:41:38.198 --> 00:41:40.995
a "Mechanic with
psychiatric delusions."

660
00:41:41.130 --> 00:41:43.634
Carter. show him.

661
00:41:43.769 --> 00:41:45.203
Yeah. right.

662
00:41:52.044 --> 00:41:53.549
Right. well. first of all..

663
00:41:53.684 --> 00:41:54.746
...you're not fighting an army.

664
00:41:54.882 --> 00:41:56.121
You have to think of this

665
00:41:56.256 --> 00:41:58.590
as a single organism.

666
00:41:58.725 --> 00:42:01.685
Now these common drones.
they act like its claws.

667
00:42:01.820 --> 00:42:03.288
And Alphas..

668
00:42:03.424 --> 00:42:05.896
...like the one that you
killed are much more rare.

669
00:42:06.031 --> 00:42:08.359
Yeah. they're like one in
6.18 million by my guess.

670
00:42:08.494 --> 00:42:10.701
'Yes.
They act as the enemy's--'

671
00:42:10.836 --> 00:42:12.466
They're like its
central nervous system.

672
00:42:12.602 --> 00:42:16.636
But this...is the brain.

673
00:42:16.771 --> 00:42:18.407
It controls them all.

674
00:42:18.542 --> 00:42:20.743
And this is the Omega.

675
00:42:20.879 --> 00:42:24.744
And the Omega has
the ability to control time.

676
00:42:24.879 --> 00:42:27.848
Whenever an Alpha is killed

677
00:42:27.984 --> 00:42:30.555
an automatic
response is triggered.

678
00:42:30.690 --> 00:42:33.349
The Omega starts
the day over again.

679
00:42:33.485 --> 00:42:35.693
But you see. this time
it can remember

680
00:42:35.828 --> 00:42:38.563
what's going to happen
just like you do.

681
00:42:38.698 --> 00:42:39.923
It knows exactly
what we're gonna do

682
00:42:40.059 --> 00:42:41.022
before we're gonna do it.

683
00:42:41.158 --> 00:42:42.057
And an enemy that knows

684
00:42:42.192 --> 00:42:44.130
the future can't lose.

685
00:42:47.499 --> 00:42:49.239
But if that's true.
how did you win at Verdun?

686
00:42:49.375 --> 00:42:51.742
We were allowed to win.

687
00:42:51.877 --> 00:42:54.813
This thing wants us
to believe we can win.

688
00:42:54.948 --> 00:42:57.739
'It wants us to throw everything
we have into the invasion.'

689
00:42:57.875 --> 00:43:03.117
Operation Downfall isn't
our endgame. it's the enemy's.

690
00:43:03.252 --> 00:43:06.252
The thing you've got
to understand is this is a..

691
00:43:06.387 --> 00:43:10.760
...perfectly evolved.
world conquering organism.

692
00:43:10.895 --> 00:43:12.187
For all we know.
there are thousands

693
00:43:12.322 --> 00:43:13.828
millions of those asteroids

694
00:43:13.964 --> 00:43:16.659
floating around in
the cosmos like a virus.

695
00:43:16.795 --> 00:43:18.798
'And they're just waiting
to crash-land into a world'

696
00:43:18.933 --> 00:43:20.672
with just the right conditions.

697
00:43:20.807 --> 00:43:23.074
All they need is for
the dominant life form

698
00:43:23.209 --> 00:43:24.809
to attack and..

699
00:43:24.944 --> 00:43:26.303
'And there'll be nothing
to stop the mimics'

700
00:43:26.439 --> 00:43:29.272
from conquering
the rest of the world.

701
00:43:29.407 --> 00:43:33.511
- Unless you change the outcome.
- Me?

702
00:43:33.647 --> 00:43:35.749
When you killed that Alpha.
you inadvertently entered

703
00:43:35.884 --> 00:43:36.849
the enemy's nervous system.

704
00:43:36.984 --> 00:43:39.284
Cage. you've seized control

705
00:43:39.419 --> 00:43:42.419
of the Omega's ability
to reset the day.

706
00:43:43.562 --> 00:43:44.694
How's that even possible?

707
00:43:44.830 --> 00:43:46.521
Perhaps this organism's
only vulnerability

708
00:43:46.657 --> 00:43:50.098
i-it's only vulnerability
is humanity.

709
00:43:50.233 --> 00:43:54.030
Regardless of that.
you control the power now

710
00:43:54.166 --> 00:43:56.835
'just as I did in Verdun.'

711
00:43:56.971 --> 00:43:58.908
So I'm resetting the day?

712
00:44:00.839 --> 00:44:03.038
Okay.

713
00:44:03.174 --> 00:44:05.079
How do I control it?

714
00:44:07.286 --> 00:44:09.017
You have to die.

715
00:44:09.717 --> 00:44:11.048
Every day.

716
00:44:11.183 --> 00:44:13.252
Until the Omega's destroyed.

717
00:44:26.097 --> 00:44:27.331
First of all..

718
00:44:27.466 --> 00:44:29.701
...this is a terrific
presentation.

719
00:44:29.836 --> 00:44:32.200
Terrific.

720
00:44:32.335 --> 00:44:34.071
'I know the general.'

721
00:44:34.207 --> 00:44:36.042
'We should take this to him.'

722
00:44:36.178 --> 00:44:38.847
You just tell him
everything you told me.

723
00:44:38.983 --> 00:44:40.713
I went to see
the general. Cage.

724
00:44:40.849 --> 00:44:42.413
Any number of times.

725
00:44:43.687 --> 00:44:45.387
Psych ward. Dissection.

726
00:44:45.522 --> 00:44:47.022
Remember?

727
00:44:49.619 --> 00:44:52.555
What are you expecting
from me?

728
00:44:54.931 --> 00:44:56.900
Have you seen
anything strange?

729
00:44:58.261 --> 00:44:59.702
Is he shitting me?

730
00:44:59.837 --> 00:45:01.035
- Visions.
- Uh. visions.

731
00:45:01.170 --> 00:45:04.239
Have you seen any
visions like that?

732
00:45:04.375 --> 00:45:06.876
The Omega senses when it's
losing control of its power.

733
00:45:07.012 --> 00:45:09.442
E-even now it's mentally
searching to find you.

734
00:45:09.578 --> 00:45:13.043
When it's close to finding you.
you will start having visions.

735
00:45:13.179 --> 00:45:14.309
You'll start to see that.

736
00:45:14.444 --> 00:45:16.645
Eh. you'll even see where it is.

737
00:45:18.855 --> 00:45:20.288
And you had these visions?

738
00:45:20.424 --> 00:45:21.650
Yes.

739
00:45:24.461 --> 00:45:27.858
But eventually you saw it.
I mean. you actually saw it.

740
00:45:27.994 --> 00:45:29.427
'Right?'

741
00:45:31.669 --> 00:45:33.563
Never in the flesh.

742
00:45:37.567 --> 00:45:40.541
So this is all
just some..

743
00:45:40.676 --> 00:45:42.372
...theory.

744
00:45:42.508 --> 00:45:44.981
You don't know
if this thing even exists.

745
00:45:45.116 --> 00:45:46.878
The visions showed me
it was at Verdun.

746
00:45:47.014 --> 00:45:49.614
I could see it. I..

747
00:45:49.750 --> 00:45:51.283
I just..

748
00:45:51.418 --> 00:45:53.418
...lost the power
before I could get to it.

749
00:45:55.255 --> 00:45:58.494
And by the time
we took Verdun..

750
00:45:58.629 --> 00:46:00.590
...the Omega was gone.

751
00:46:03.097 --> 00:46:05.360
Okay. so all I have to do is..

752
00:46:05.496 --> 00:46:07.431
...wait to have
these visions

753
00:46:07.566 --> 00:46:11.032
and then tell you where
this Omega thing is.

754
00:46:11.167 --> 00:46:13.510
No. Cage.

755
00:46:13.646 --> 00:46:15.875
You're gonna get me there..

756
00:46:16.010 --> 00:46:17.277
...and I'm gonna kill it.

757
00:46:18.615 --> 00:46:20.316
Get you there?

758
00:46:20.451 --> 00:46:21.949
I'm not..

759
00:46:22.084 --> 00:46:24.548
I'm not even
trained for combat.

760
00:46:39.940 --> 00:46:43.006
'Reload. Reload.'

761
00:47:02.188 --> 00:47:04.220
Are you alright. Cage?

762
00:47:04.356 --> 00:47:06.022
I think I broke something.

763
00:47:06.158 --> 00:47:07.890
'What?'

764
00:47:08.026 --> 00:47:10.429
My back.

765
00:47:10.564 --> 00:47:13.533
The only thing I can feel
are my-my lips.

766
00:47:13.668 --> 00:47:17.200
Now listen carefully.
This is a very important rule.

767
00:47:17.335 --> 00:47:19.342
This is the only rule.

768
00:47:19.478 --> 00:47:22.905
You get injured on the field.
you better make sure you die.

769
00:47:23.041 --> 00:47:23.943
Why?

770
00:47:24.079 --> 00:47:26.284
Last time I was in combat

771
00:47:26.419 --> 00:47:28.084
I was hit.

772
00:47:28.219 --> 00:47:31.017
I was bleeding out.
just not fast enough.

773
00:47:31.153 --> 00:47:32.981
I woke up in a field hospital

774
00:47:33.117 --> 00:47:37.653
with three pints of someone
else's blood and I was out.

775
00:47:37.788 --> 00:47:41.592
I lost the power.
Do you understand?

776
00:47:41.727 --> 00:47:43.266
I think we better start over.
Don't you?

777
00:47:43.402 --> 00:47:44.566
What?

778
00:47:48.573 --> 00:47:50.998
No one knows what
happened to Private Cage!

779
00:47:51.133 --> 00:47:52.867
Skinner. you dumb-ass.
He was right next to you.

780
00:47:53.003 --> 00:47:54.073
You're tellin' me
you don't know where that

781
00:47:54.209 --> 00:47:55.610
slippery son of a bitch went?

782
00:47:55.745 --> 00:47:57.181
No. sarge!

783
00:47:57.317 --> 00:47:58.946
Alright.

784
00:47:59.082 --> 00:48:01.284
Let's do another 50. shall we?

785
00:48:01.420 --> 00:48:02.644
And one!

786
00:48:02.779 --> 00:48:04.748
No. wait! Wait.
My name is Bill Cage.

787
00:48:04.883 --> 00:48:08.250
I.. We met on the beach.
We meet on the beach tomorrow.

788
00:48:08.385 --> 00:48:09.393
I have what you had.

789
00:48:15.602 --> 00:48:18.061
Alright. let's go again.

790
00:48:21.140 --> 00:48:23.735
You don't have time to think.
Remember.

791
00:48:23.870 --> 00:48:25.910
'It's not enough knowing
where they're going to be.'

792
00:48:26.045 --> 00:48:27.774
'You have to know
how to kill them.'

793
00:48:33.082 --> 00:48:34.617
I just. hold on.
Hold on.

794
00:48:34.752 --> 00:48:36.383
Listen. Listen.

795
00:48:37.853 --> 00:48:39.751
Okay. do it.

796
00:48:41.419 --> 00:48:42.426
On your feet. maggot!

797
00:48:46.958 --> 00:48:49.393
Stop! Wait!
Wait. wait. wait!

798
00:48:49.528 --> 00:48:50.900
Stop! Wait!
Wait a second!

799
00:48:51.036 --> 00:48:54.806
Wait a second.
Wait a second.

800
00:48:54.941 --> 00:48:56.566
You know.
I've been thinking.

801
00:48:56.702 --> 00:49:00.237
I mean. this thing's
in my blood.

802
00:49:00.373 --> 00:49:01.975
So maybe there's some way

803
00:49:02.111 --> 00:49:03.871
I can transfer it to you.

804
00:49:04.007 --> 00:49:06.440
I've tried everything.
It doesn't work.

805
00:49:06.575 --> 00:49:09.178
I mean. have you..

806
00:49:09.314 --> 00:49:11.114
...you know..

807
00:49:11.250 --> 00:49:12.655
...tried all..

808
00:49:12.791 --> 00:49:14.188
...all the options.

809
00:49:14.324 --> 00:49:17.487
Oh. you mean sex.
Yep. Tried it.

810
00:49:17.623 --> 00:49:19.727
- How many times?
- Alright.

811
00:49:22.362 --> 00:49:25.368
Left. left!
Left. left. le..

812
00:49:27.839 --> 00:49:29.165
Keep your eyes open.

813
00:49:31.972 --> 00:49:33.675
Again.

814
00:49:33.811 --> 00:49:36.344
Again. Again.

815
00:49:38.979 --> 00:49:40.341
Again.

816
00:49:46.752 --> 00:49:48.690
'Just wait! Wait!
I think I'm okay.'

817
00:49:50.955 --> 00:49:53.658
On your feet. maggot!
Maggot! Maggot!

818
00:49:53.794 --> 00:49:56.694
Now. I'm tryin' to be nice
to you. maggot! Now. move!

819
00:49:59.029 --> 00:50:00.494
- Are you okay. Cage?
- Oh. yeah. yeah!

820
00:50:00.630 --> 00:50:01.802
I'm good! I'm good!

821
00:50:01.938 --> 00:50:02.972
Your leg's broken.

822
00:50:03.107 --> 00:50:05.439
No. I-I can still feel my toes.

823
00:50:06.744 --> 00:50:09.106
Oh. come on.

824
00:50:28.698 --> 00:50:31.526
Rita. R-Rita. what is this?
What are you doing here?

825
00:50:31.662 --> 00:50:32.961
Who-who-who's this guy?

826
00:50:33.096 --> 00:50:35.369
- He's me...before Verdun.
- Before Verdun.

827
00:50:35.504 --> 00:50:37.374
- What-what do you mean? He's..
- Yes. Yes.

828
00:50:37.509 --> 00:50:40.010
- When did he die? Where?
- On the beach. Tomorrow.

829
00:50:40.146 --> 00:50:41.274
I'm Bill Cage.
You're Dr. Carter.

830
00:50:41.409 --> 00:50:42.672
We've had this
conversation before.

831
00:50:42.807 --> 00:50:44.241
You have two fingers
behind your back.

832
00:50:44.376 --> 00:50:45.583
I've had the visions.

833
00:50:45.718 --> 00:50:47.448
I've seen the Omega.

834
00:50:50.423 --> 00:50:53.017
Um..

835
00:50:53.152 --> 00:50:54.552
It's..

836
00:50:54.688 --> 00:50:55.793
...pretty much
game over tomorrow.

837
00:50:55.928 --> 00:50:57.862
So. can we move this along?

838
00:50:57.997 --> 00:51:01.356
Okay. Okay. Where?

839
00:51:01.492 --> 00:51:03.090
There's a dam.

840
00:51:03.226 --> 00:51:05.401
It's in the mountains.
I saw German writing.

841
00:51:05.536 --> 00:51:07.266
'Do you think you can
work out where that is?'

842
00:51:07.401 --> 00:51:09.006
Well. I mean. there can't be

843
00:51:09.142 --> 00:51:10.773
too many places that fit
that description.

844
00:51:10.909 --> 00:51:12.466
I'll see what I can do.

845
00:51:12.601 --> 00:51:14.074
Training's over.

846
00:51:14.209 --> 00:51:15.836
I'll see you tomorrow.

847
00:51:15.972 --> 00:51:17.076
We don't even know
where we're going.

848
00:51:17.212 --> 00:51:18.907
We will soon enough.

849
00:51:19.043 --> 00:51:20.114
In the meantime.
you need to figure out

850
00:51:20.249 --> 00:51:22.351
a way to get us off that beach.

851
00:51:43.372 --> 00:51:45.272
What next?

852
00:51:45.407 --> 00:51:46.404
- Where we going?
- Yeah.

853
00:51:46.539 --> 00:51:47.945
Which way? Focus.
Which way?

854
00:51:48.081 --> 00:51:48.977
I'm thinking.
I'm thinking.

855
00:51:49.113 --> 00:51:51.781
- Okay.
- Oh. man!

856
00:51:51.917 --> 00:51:54.013
How far did we make it?

857
00:51:54.148 --> 00:51:55.809
You know. it's..

858
00:51:55.945 --> 00:51:57.247
...hard to say. really. It's..

859
00:51:58.790 --> 00:52:01.185
Hold! Hold!

860
00:52:01.320 --> 00:52:03.957
Okay. go!

861
00:52:04.092 --> 00:52:05.523
Son of a bitch!

862
00:52:05.658 --> 00:52:06.988
I thought stepping left.
ducking..

863
00:52:07.123 --> 00:52:08.530
Just for the record.
stepping left. ducking--

864
00:52:08.665 --> 00:52:10.658
Stepping left. ducking right.
Stepping right.

865
00:52:10.794 --> 00:52:13.536
Stepping left. ducking right.

866
00:52:13.672 --> 00:52:14.964
Move on.

867
00:52:18.109 --> 00:52:18.975
'Hold on!'

868
00:52:19.110 --> 00:52:21.035
Now. remember. cross the trench

869
00:52:21.170 --> 00:52:23.742
12 o'clock then
look to your right!

870
00:52:30.322 --> 00:52:32.222
You're not being specific.
Do you understand?

871
00:52:32.357 --> 00:52:34.085
You need to be specific.
otherwise. I'm dead.

872
00:52:34.221 --> 00:52:36.326
Just.. Rita.

873
00:52:38.158 --> 00:52:39.395
Cage!

874
00:52:41.298 --> 00:52:43.323
Paces up to the top
of the trench.

875
00:52:43.459 --> 00:52:45.031
I'm gonna step left there's
gonna be a mimic there

876
00:52:45.166 --> 00:52:46.061
which I'll kill.

877
00:52:55.471 --> 00:52:58.315
Ship explosion. I'm gonna
run 30 paces Northwest.

878
00:52:58.450 --> 00:53:00.049
I'm gonna duck at
the top of that trench

879
00:53:00.184 --> 00:53:02.715
and then
I'm gonna turn left.

880
00:53:10.890 --> 00:53:13.055
Have I got something
on my face?

881
00:53:14.931 --> 00:53:16.564
No.

882
00:53:23.842 --> 00:53:27.069
'Cage. we've been lookin'
everywhere for you!'

883
00:53:27.911 --> 00:53:29.275
Cage!

884
00:53:29.411 --> 00:53:30.977
Cage. we've been lookin'..

885
00:53:31.112 --> 00:53:32.111
Guys..

886
00:53:32.247 --> 00:53:33.774
Guys. can we..

887
00:53:33.910 --> 00:53:36.712
...just not do this today?

888
00:53:36.847 --> 00:53:38.652
What are you talkin' about?

889
00:53:38.787 --> 00:53:40.153
Farell almost strung
us up by our bollocks

890
00:53:40.289 --> 00:53:41.591
for losing track of you!

891
00:53:43.755 --> 00:53:46.022
Okay. Skinner. watch this.

892
00:53:47.397 --> 00:53:49.261
Now. I'm gonna close my eyes.

893
00:53:49.396 --> 00:53:51.359
- Ready?
- Yeah.

894
00:53:55.865 --> 00:53:58.240
'Stinking bastard.'

895
00:53:58.376 --> 00:54:01.405
I-I didn't mind
the extra push-ups.

896
00:54:10.587 --> 00:54:12.921
'It's a new day. people.'

897
00:54:13.057 --> 00:54:14.655
Destiny calls.

898
00:54:14.790 --> 00:54:16.926
The world expects only
one thing from us

899
00:54:17.061 --> 00:54:18.857
that we will win.

900
00:54:33.769 --> 00:54:36.105
'The current situation
on the front line.'

901
00:54:36.241 --> 00:54:38.507
'Our troops have suffered
heavy casualties.'

902
00:54:38.643 --> 00:54:41.108
'It's about time we showed those
things what we're made of.'

903
00:54:41.244 --> 00:54:43.982
'My father flew in
the battle of Britain.'

904
00:54:44.118 --> 00:54:47.081
'Three years before
the yanks came into the war.'

905
00:54:47.216 --> 00:54:50.190
'Couldn't be broken.
Backbone.'

906
00:54:50.325 --> 00:54:53.630
'My Uncle George landed
on the beach at Normandy.'

907
00:54:53.766 --> 00:54:56.761
'In their day. this war would
have been over by now.'

908
00:54:56.897 --> 00:54:58.696
What do they want
with us. anyway?

909
00:54:58.831 --> 00:55:00.667
It's obvious. isn't it?
Minerals.

910
00:55:00.803 --> 00:55:01.865
- Minerals?
- Yeah. minerals. Metals.

911
00:55:02.000 --> 00:55:03.770
- Oxygen. they want.
- Oxygen?

912
00:55:03.905 --> 00:55:06.208
- Think about it.
- What difference does it make?

913
00:55:06.344 --> 00:55:08.676
They're here.
They're winning.

914
00:55:08.811 --> 00:55:11.543
And whatever it is.
they're gonna get it.

915
00:55:11.678 --> 00:55:14.446
Shouldn't you be over there?

916
00:55:14.581 --> 00:55:16.645
I've been over there.

917
00:55:16.781 --> 00:55:18.819
More times than anybody.

918
00:55:18.955 --> 00:55:23.053
As a matter of fact.
I'm usually long dead by now.

919
00:55:25.622 --> 00:55:27.255
Coward!

920
00:55:29.863 --> 00:55:31.158
'What's going on?'

921
00:55:31.293 --> 00:55:32.363
'The power's gone.'

922
00:56:41.072 --> 00:56:43.771
I found the Omega. I found it.
It has to be here.

923
00:56:43.907 --> 00:56:46.001
Curnera Dam. Germany.
This has got to be it.

924
00:56:46.136 --> 00:56:47.142
It fit's the description
perfectly.

925
00:56:47.277 --> 00:56:48.636
Yes. you found it.

926
00:56:48.771 --> 00:56:50.246
Again.

927
00:56:50.382 --> 00:56:52.272
What difference does it make?

928
00:56:52.408 --> 00:56:54.078
'Cause we're never
gonna get there.

929
00:56:55.583 --> 00:56:57.486
No matter what we do

930
00:56:57.622 --> 00:57:00.751
no matter how
carefully we plan..

931
00:57:00.886 --> 00:57:03.124
...we can't get off that beach.

932
00:57:13.305 --> 00:57:16.100
You can do this.
You can.

933
00:57:16.235 --> 00:57:19.437
You keep coming here every day
and I'll train you.

934
00:57:22.147 --> 00:57:24.141
You already have.

935
00:57:43.033 --> 00:57:45.998
- I'm waitin'. Nance!
- 500 meters and closing fast!

936
00:57:47.196 --> 00:57:48.462
What the..!

937
00:57:57.109 --> 00:57:58.373
'Reload.'

938
00:58:10.161 --> 00:58:11.452
What's next?

939
00:58:13.497 --> 00:58:16.130
Straight shot...up the hill.

940
00:58:16.265 --> 00:58:17.992
Okay.

941
00:58:18.127 --> 00:58:20.995
Hey. sarge. the new guy..

942
00:58:21.130 --> 00:58:22.903
...what's his name again?

943
00:58:26.339 --> 00:58:28.938
'We'll need a vehicle
to get further inland.'

944
00:58:29.074 --> 00:58:30.004
And what's the problem?

945
00:58:30.140 --> 00:58:31.247
The problem is the ambush

946
00:58:31.383 --> 00:58:32.715
waiting for us down there.

947
00:58:32.850 --> 00:58:34.384
They kill us before
we find a working car.

948
00:58:34.519 --> 00:58:36.882
Okay.
So. what's the current plan?

949
00:58:37.018 --> 00:58:38.188
The two cars
we haven't tried yet.

950
00:58:38.324 --> 00:58:39.455
- 'The minivan.'
- 'Yep.'

951
00:58:39.591 --> 00:58:41.625
- 'The green S.U.V.'
- Okay.

952
00:58:41.760 --> 00:58:43.391
So I'll head for the S.U.V..
draw the mimics to me

953
00:58:43.527 --> 00:58:44.589
you go for the minivan.

954
00:58:44.724 --> 00:58:46.057
You get it started

955
00:58:46.193 --> 00:58:47.757
just go. take off.
Do not wait for me.

956
00:58:47.892 --> 00:58:49.124
- Okay.
- Whoa..

957
00:58:49.259 --> 00:58:51.928
Just don't forget to disconnect

958
00:58:52.063 --> 00:58:53.468
the caravan before you take off.

959
00:58:53.604 --> 00:58:54.801
You are going to be in a hurry

960
00:58:54.937 --> 00:58:57.106
and you don't want
any dead weight.

961
00:59:22.232 --> 00:59:24.530
Come on.

962
00:59:38.217 --> 00:59:40.249
Come on. Cage!

963
00:59:40.385 --> 00:59:42.916
'Our troops have suffered
heavy casualties.'

964
00:59:43.051 --> 00:59:45.187
'The enemy has breached
security at Dover.'

965
00:59:45.322 --> 00:59:46.590
I can't see.

966
00:59:46.726 --> 00:59:47.587
'To seek shelter'

967
00:59:47.723 --> 00:59:48.782
'as a matter of urgency.'

968
00:59:48.918 --> 00:59:50.420
Can you?

969
00:59:50.556 --> 00:59:51.492
'Mimics have now been sighted'

970
00:59:51.628 --> 00:59:53.495
'at Portsmouth. Brighton'

971
00:59:53.630 --> 00:59:56.831
'and as far inland as Horsham.'

972
00:59:56.966 --> 00:59:58.559
'The government advice
at this point'

973
00:59:58.695 --> 01:00:01.271
'is to stay where you are
and remain calm.'

974
01:00:01.407 --> 01:00:02.738
'If you are in a vehicle'

975
01:00:02.873 --> 01:00:05.333
'please lock doors
and stay inside.'

976
01:00:05.469 --> 01:00:07.973
'We are-are now
hearing accounts'

977
01:00:08.109 --> 01:00:11.107
'of mimic attacks
at Canterbury. Farnham'

978
01:00:11.242 --> 01:00:13.977
'and we.. we..
I'm sorry.'

979
01:00:14.112 --> 01:00:15.914
'The enemy has reached London.'

980
01:00:16.049 --> 01:00:18.583
'Repeat.
London is under attack.'

981
01:00:23.823 --> 01:00:25.089
It's good driving.

982
01:00:25.224 --> 01:00:27.788
I forgot
to unhook the trailer.

983
01:00:41.372 --> 01:00:43.509
'Engaged.'

984
01:01:12.872 --> 01:01:14.712
You don't talk much.

985
01:01:15.710 --> 01:01:17.146
I'm not a fan.

986
01:01:17.282 --> 01:01:18.711
Of talking?

987
01:01:18.847 --> 01:01:20.542
Not a fan of talking. No.

988
01:01:22.215 --> 01:01:24.546
You know. you eventually
do talk to me.

989
01:01:26.458 --> 01:01:27.390
It's usually around Lyon

990
01:01:27.526 --> 01:01:28.820
you tell me about the time you

991
01:01:28.956 --> 01:01:30.260
went there with your family.

992
01:01:30.395 --> 01:01:32.389
Your brother got lost.

993
01:01:34.158 --> 01:01:36.432
I've never been to Lyon.

994
01:01:36.568 --> 01:01:38.934
You tell me your middle name.

995
01:01:39.930 --> 01:01:41.563
Peyton.

996
01:01:43.366 --> 01:01:45.204
That's not my middle name.

997
01:01:50.113 --> 01:01:52.442
You found your brother
in the arcade. by the way.

998
01:01:54.614 --> 01:01:56.881
Well. maybe I made it all up
just to keep you quiet.

999
01:01:57.016 --> 01:01:58.281
But you do talk to me.

1000
01:01:58.417 --> 01:02:00.383
Cage. I do not need
to get to know you.

1001
01:02:00.519 --> 01:02:01.792
And if you knew
what was good for you

1002
01:02:01.927 --> 01:02:03.894
you wouldn't wanna
get to know me either.

1003
01:02:04.029 --> 01:02:07.092
It's the only way you make
it through this thing.

1004
01:02:07.228 --> 01:02:09.933
What about Hendricks?
You get to know him?

1005
01:02:10.068 --> 01:02:13.036
- How do you know that name?
- You mentioned him.

1006
01:02:13.171 --> 01:02:15.366
- That's not possible.
- Then how do I know his name?

1007
01:02:15.501 --> 01:02:18.138
When did I mention him?
Under what circumstance?

1008
01:02:19.710 --> 01:02:21.911
Is he why you won't talk to me?

1009
01:02:25.510 --> 01:02:28.884
Don't ever mention
his name again.

1010
01:02:29.019 --> 01:02:31.613
- Why? Are you in love with him?
- He's dead.

1011
01:02:35.389 --> 01:02:39.191
And I watched him die 300 times.
and I remember..

1012
01:02:39.327 --> 01:02:41.126
...every detail.
I remember everything.

1013
01:02:41.262 --> 01:02:43.328
So I don't need
to talk about it.

1014
01:02:48.603 --> 01:02:50.031
I'm sorry.

1015
01:02:50.167 --> 01:02:52.139
It's just war.

1016
01:03:54.907 --> 01:03:57.204
There's nothing here.
Let's keep going.

1017
01:04:20.490 --> 01:04:22.994
We have to find the keys.

1018
01:04:23.130 --> 01:04:24.326
Let's just siphon the gas.

1019
01:04:24.462 --> 01:04:26.897
Oh. why drive
when we can fly?

1020
01:04:27.033 --> 01:04:28.334
In that thing?

1021
01:04:28.469 --> 01:04:30.605
Let me guess.
You're afraid of heights.

1022
01:04:30.741 --> 01:04:32.171
I'm afraid of crashing.

1023
01:04:32.307 --> 01:04:33.844
And not at all
ashamed to admit it.

1024
01:04:33.979 --> 01:04:36.540
You'll be fine. Cage.
You'll learn.

1025
01:04:38.050 --> 01:04:41.244
- What is it?
- It's nothing. I'm fine.

1026
01:04:41.380 --> 01:04:42.978
- What is it?
- It's nothing.

1027
01:04:43.113 --> 01:04:44.746
Rita.

1028
01:04:47.888 --> 01:04:49.487
Let me see.

1029
01:05:09.377 --> 01:05:11.046
We have to find the keys
to the helicopter.

1030
01:05:11.181 --> 01:05:13.949
Yeah. I'm sure they're
around here somewhere.

1031
01:05:14.085 --> 01:05:15.946
You know the heli's
full of fuel. though.

1032
01:05:16.081 --> 01:05:18.279
I found a hose.

1033
01:05:18.415 --> 01:05:20.122
We're flying. Cage.

1034
01:05:24.029 --> 01:05:26.127
Let's just say
we find the keys.

1035
01:05:26.263 --> 01:05:29.659
You know. get that
helicopter started.

1036
01:05:29.794 --> 01:05:32.164
We don't have our
jackets or ammunition.

1037
01:05:32.299 --> 01:05:34.664
It's gonna be dark
in a few hours.

1038
01:05:36.605 --> 01:05:39.302
Might be better off just
going back to the farmhouse.

1039
01:05:39.438 --> 01:05:41.504
Seeing what we could salvage.

1040
01:05:41.640 --> 01:05:43.680
You know.
spend the night there.

1041
01:05:43.816 --> 01:05:44.943
Come back here in the morning.

1042
01:05:45.079 --> 01:05:46.110
And curl up by the fire

1043
01:05:46.245 --> 01:05:48.051
and open a bottle of wine?

1044
01:05:51.824 --> 01:05:53.824
I think we should just reset.

1045
01:05:53.959 --> 01:05:55.489
- Whoa! It's a dead end.
- Hey. just..

1046
01:05:55.624 --> 01:05:58.052
If it's all the same to you.
I'm tired. I'm in pain.

1047
01:05:58.187 --> 01:05:59.562
- I'd rather just start fresh.
- I'll tell you what.

1048
01:05:59.698 --> 01:06:01.362
Take a few minutes.

1049
01:06:01.497 --> 01:06:03.790
Coffee's ready.
I'll look around for the keys.

1050
01:06:03.926 --> 01:06:05.661
- That's productive.
- Ten minutes.

1051
01:06:05.796 --> 01:06:08.569
- Okay.
- And then I'm killing you.

1052
01:06:08.704 --> 01:06:09.668
Fine.

1053
01:06:13.441 --> 01:06:15.672
I can't believe
you found coffee.

1054
01:06:17.241 --> 01:06:19.546
Thank you.

1055
01:06:19.682 --> 01:06:21.847
Oh.

1056
01:06:21.983 --> 01:06:23.177
Sugar. right?

1057
01:06:23.312 --> 01:06:24.714
Yeah.

1058
01:06:30.126 --> 01:06:31.486
- Thank you.
- Ah. hold on.

1059
01:06:31.622 --> 01:06:33.789
Three.
You like three.

1060
01:06:46.971 --> 01:06:49.673
There's a shirt over there.
It should be your size.

1061
01:06:57.719 --> 01:07:00.189
'How many times
have we been here?'

1062
01:07:06.059 --> 01:07:08.290
How many times?

1063
01:07:08.425 --> 01:07:11.024
Where are the keys?

1064
01:07:11.160 --> 01:07:13.129
- Where are the goddamn keys?
- Yeah. okay.

1065
01:07:14.863 --> 01:07:17.667
You can fly it. can't you?

1066
01:07:17.803 --> 01:07:20.241
No. Well. yes.
I mean. I can take off.

1067
01:07:20.377 --> 01:07:21.871
I'm still working
on my landing. so..

1068
01:07:22.007 --> 01:07:24.277
What are we still doing here?
You're wasting time!

1069
01:07:24.412 --> 01:07:27.249
Rita. if you start
that engine you die.

1070
01:07:30.513 --> 01:07:32.446
This is far as you go

1071
01:07:32.581 --> 01:07:34.947
no matter what I do.

1072
01:07:35.083 --> 01:07:37.292
This is as far
as you ever make it.

1073
01:07:45.027 --> 01:07:48.434
There's a mimic buried
20 yards away.

1074
01:07:48.570 --> 01:07:50.404
It attacks when
you start the engine.

1075
01:07:51.903 --> 01:07:54.440
Get your weapon and get
in the helicopter. Cage.

1076
01:07:54.576 --> 01:07:56.740
There's more in
the field back there.

1077
01:07:59.107 --> 01:08:00.842
- Only one of us ever makes it.
- Get in.

1078
01:08:00.978 --> 01:08:02.417
The only thing we haven't tried
is the version

1079
01:08:02.552 --> 01:08:04.119
where you walk away. We just go
back to the farmhouse.

1080
01:08:04.255 --> 01:08:05.481
'There's a cellar.
There's food.'

1081
01:08:05.616 --> 01:08:07.480
You wait there till I get back.

1082
01:08:07.615 --> 01:08:08.683
You'll be safe.

1083
01:08:08.819 --> 01:08:10.950
I'm a soldier.
I volunteered.

1084
01:08:11.086 --> 01:08:13.420
- I'm not walking away.
- You die here.

1085
01:08:13.555 --> 01:08:14.531
Right here.

1086
01:08:15.658 --> 01:08:18.597
I...can't save you.

1087
01:08:18.732 --> 01:08:22.163
And if I go on and kill
the Omega. you're dead.

1088
01:08:22.299 --> 01:08:23.568
Forever.

1089
01:08:23.704 --> 01:08:26.000
Why does it matter
what happens to me?

1090
01:08:29.647 --> 01:08:31.506
I wish..

1091
01:08:31.641 --> 01:08:33.612
...I didn't know you..

1092
01:08:35.214 --> 01:08:36.912
...but I do.

1093
01:10:07.570 --> 01:10:10.240
My middle name..

1094
01:10:10.375 --> 01:10:12.282
...is Rose.

1095
01:10:32.029 --> 01:10:33.859
On your feet. maggot!

1096
01:10:44.883 --> 01:10:47.107
'The good news is there's
hope for you. private.'

1097
01:10:47.243 --> 01:10:50.085
'Hope in the form
of glorious combat.'

1098
01:10:50.221 --> 01:10:51.785
Battle is the great redeemer.

1099
01:10:51.920 --> 01:10:55.420
The fiery crucible in which the
only true heroes are forged.

1100
01:10:55.556 --> 01:10:56.821
The one place where all men..

1101
01:11:07.134 --> 01:11:09.137
Yes?

1102
01:11:09.272 --> 01:11:11.539
'Who said you could talk to me?'

1103
01:11:14.677 --> 01:11:17.380
Have I got something
on my face. soldier?

1104
01:11:20.308 --> 01:11:22.385
I'm sorry to disturb you.
sergeant.

1105
01:11:44.267 --> 01:11:45.368
Alright. man. let's get
this show on the road.

1106
01:11:45.503 --> 01:11:47.038
I gotta suit up.

1107
01:11:47.173 --> 01:11:49.538
'Come on. Kimmel.
let's have it!'

1108
01:11:49.673 --> 01:11:50.875
Where's your helmet?

1109
01:11:52.609 --> 01:11:54.308
Never wear one.

1110
01:11:54.443 --> 01:11:58.914
- It's a distraction.
- Have you been drinking?

1111
01:11:59.050 --> 01:12:01.685
I need three more
clips of 5-5-6

1112
01:12:01.821 --> 01:12:04.988
eight grenades
and an extra battery.

1113
01:12:08.492 --> 01:12:10.195
Get it.

1114
01:12:16.405 --> 01:12:17.532
'Oi!'

1115
01:12:17.667 --> 01:12:19.102
'Oi. mate!'

1116
01:12:19.237 --> 01:12:22.572
I think there's something
wrong with your suit.

1117
01:12:22.708 --> 01:12:25.079
There's a dead guy in it.

1118
01:12:25.215 --> 01:12:27.511
Woo-hoo! We made it!

1119
01:12:27.646 --> 01:12:29.510
Thank God. we made it!

1120
01:12:29.645 --> 01:12:30.849
Whoo..

1121
01:14:32.010 --> 01:14:33.967
Finish it!

1122
01:15:28.099 --> 01:15:29.356
It isn't there.

1123
01:15:29.492 --> 01:15:30.760
What do you mean
the Omega isn't there?

1124
01:15:30.896 --> 01:15:32.366
My guess is. it never was.

1125
01:15:32.501 --> 01:15:33.695
They knew we were coming.

1126
01:15:33.831 --> 01:15:34.763
They ambushed us.

1127
01:15:34.899 --> 01:15:36.606
The visions were a trap.

1128
01:15:38.138 --> 01:15:40.676
Just like Rita's visions
were a trap at Verdun.

1129
01:15:41.975 --> 01:15:43.736
It could have killed me.
but it didn't.

1130
01:15:43.872 --> 01:15:45.882
- It's was after my blood.
- So they know who you are.

1131
01:15:46.017 --> 01:15:47.877
They..

1132
01:15:48.012 --> 01:15:49.210
They want their power back.

1133
01:15:49.346 --> 01:15:50.912
And they're gonna get it
one way or another

1134
01:15:51.047 --> 01:15:52.678
unless we find the Omega.

1135
01:15:52.813 --> 01:15:55.190
The.. There isn't any
other way. we're finished.

1136
01:15:55.326 --> 01:15:57.088
No. we're not finished.

1137
01:15:57.224 --> 01:15:58.427
That doesn't work.
I-I can't get it to work.

1138
01:15:58.563 --> 01:16:00.025
You built a prototype
at Whitehall--

1139
01:16:00.160 --> 01:16:02.930
Yes. and I got fired for it.
thank you very much.

1140
01:16:03.065 --> 01:16:04.964
- Wh-what is this thing. anyway?
- 'It's a transponder.'

1141
01:16:05.100 --> 01:16:06.768
You stick it into
the Alpha and it taps into

1142
01:16:06.903 --> 01:16:08.434
the wavelength
connecting it to the Omega.

1143
01:16:08.570 --> 01:16:10.437
That's the idea. anyway.

1144
01:16:10.573 --> 01:16:11.805
But I can't get it to work

1145
01:16:11.941 --> 01:16:14.501
not with the equipment
I have on hand.

1146
01:16:16.139 --> 01:16:17.436
How do we get you what you need?

1147
01:16:17.572 --> 01:16:18.845
Well. that's the thing.
I mean..

1148
01:16:18.980 --> 01:16:20.282
When I was at Whitehall
I built one.

1149
01:16:20.418 --> 01:16:21.681
I was even ready to test it.

1150
01:16:21.817 --> 01:16:23.478
When I told
my superiors about it..

1151
01:16:23.614 --> 01:16:26.445
- Well. I lost my job.
- They thought he was crazy.

1152
01:16:26.581 --> 01:16:28.684
So all we need to do
is go to Whitehall.

1153
01:16:28.819 --> 01:16:31.119
'He'd be arrested 10 feet
from the front door.'

1154
01:16:31.254 --> 01:16:32.595
'Psych ward. Dissection.
Remember?'

1155
01:16:32.731 --> 01:16:35.260
Hey. hey. hey!
Aren't you forgetting something?

1156
01:16:35.396 --> 01:16:38.133
The transponder requires
a live Alpha to make it work.

1157
01:16:38.269 --> 01:16:40.236
We don't need one.

1158
01:16:40.372 --> 01:16:42.430
We got the next best thing.

1159
01:16:45.233 --> 01:16:48.007
When the Chinese delegation
comes out we pick up the pace.

1160
01:16:50.312 --> 01:16:52.814
This guy with the yellow
armband always recognizes you

1161
01:16:52.949 --> 01:16:56.510
so just keep your head down
and stay to my right.

1162
01:17:02.985 --> 01:17:04.694
Nicely done.

1163
01:17:07.154 --> 01:17:08.988
Three. two. one.

1164
01:17:09.123 --> 01:17:11.701
Go. One..

1165
01:17:13.635 --> 01:17:16.530
...six. seven. eight..

1166
01:17:23.005 --> 01:17:25.738
And. turn.

1167
01:17:25.873 --> 01:17:27.882
Okay. Keep walking.
Just stare straight ahead.

1168
01:17:29.818 --> 01:17:31.585
'Robinson.'

1169
01:17:31.720 --> 01:17:33.147
I've asked not to be disturbed.

1170
01:17:33.282 --> 01:17:34.314
This had better be critical.

1171
01:17:34.449 --> 01:17:35.751
The fate of mankind.

1172
01:17:35.886 --> 01:17:37.525
Critical enough?

1173
01:17:37.660 --> 01:17:39.057
I don't believe what I'm seeing.

1174
01:17:39.192 --> 01:17:41.489
I've had more than
my share of that.

1175
01:17:41.625 --> 01:17:44.558
Sit down. general.
Stay away from the desk.

1176
01:17:44.693 --> 01:17:47.099
I'd take her very seriously
if I were you.

1177
01:17:48.870 --> 01:17:51.237
Have to hand it to you. major.

1178
01:17:51.373 --> 01:17:53.908
When you left this office today.
I never imagined you'd be back.

1179
01:17:54.043 --> 01:17:55.874
Let alone with my most
decorated soldier.

1180
01:17:56.010 --> 01:17:57.173
I'm gonna tell you
a story. general.

1181
01:17:57.309 --> 01:17:58.847
And. at first.
it's gonna sound ridiculous

1182
01:17:58.982 --> 01:18:00.745
but the longer I talk
the more rational

1183
01:18:00.880 --> 01:18:02.180
it's going to appear.

1184
01:18:02.315 --> 01:18:04.379
- Tell him you'll call back.
- Tell who?

1185
01:18:04.515 --> 01:18:06.389
Major General Beaumont.
calling from Halifax.

1186
01:18:06.524 --> 01:18:07.717
His plane has just been delayed.

1187
01:18:07.852 --> 01:18:09.255
Bad weather.

1188
01:18:09.390 --> 01:18:10.859
Yes.

1189
01:18:13.655 --> 01:18:16.095
Thank you. Beaumont.
I'll call you back.

1190
01:18:17.959 --> 01:18:19.495
Tomorrow's invasion
is a slaughter.

1191
01:18:19.631 --> 01:18:21.363
I'm dead within 5 minutes
of landing on that beach

1192
01:18:21.499 --> 01:18:23.730
along with every other
soldier you are sending.

1193
01:18:23.865 --> 01:18:26.572
and that's because
the enemy knows we're coming.

1194
01:18:26.707 --> 01:18:27.872
How do I know this?

1195
01:18:28.007 --> 01:18:29.345
Before I died. I killed a mimic

1196
01:18:29.481 --> 01:18:30.846
only this one was different.

1197
01:18:30.981 --> 01:18:33.046
It passed something
on to me in my blood.

1198
01:18:33.182 --> 01:18:35.548
Now I live the same day
over and over again.

1199
01:18:35.683 --> 01:18:36.917
Just like they do.

1200
01:18:37.053 --> 01:18:39.788
Just like Sergeant Vrataski
at Verdun.

1201
01:18:39.924 --> 01:18:42.686
Tell your secretary
everything's fine.

1202
01:18:42.821 --> 01:18:44.420
Beg your pardon?

1203
01:18:46.926 --> 01:18:48.358
Um. I'm sorry. general.

1204
01:18:48.493 --> 01:18:50.592
- I thought you were alone.
- It's fine.

1205
01:18:50.727 --> 01:18:52.558
She typed up those orders
for you to authorize

1206
01:18:52.694 --> 01:18:53.634
but she left out
the ones referring

1207
01:18:53.770 --> 01:18:55.772
to the fuel dump at Greenwich.

1208
01:18:57.837 --> 01:18:58.971
Your name is Iris.

1209
01:18:59.107 --> 01:19:01.239
'Your birthday
is September 17th.'

1210
01:19:01.374 --> 01:19:02.976
The general quietly
pulled some strings

1211
01:19:03.111 --> 01:19:04.603
stationed your only
son in Australia

1212
01:19:04.739 --> 01:19:06.740
as far from the war
as possible.

1213
01:19:06.876 --> 01:19:08.109
Tell the general his dinner's
just been cancelled.

1214
01:19:08.245 --> 01:19:10.281
The call came in just now.

1215
01:19:11.886 --> 01:19:13.686
Your dinner was cancelled.

1216
01:19:13.821 --> 01:19:16.526
You forgot the fuel dump.

1217
01:19:16.661 --> 01:19:18.795
Thank you. Iris.
That'll be all.

1218
01:19:26.465 --> 01:19:29.100
- Cage. let's go.
- Rita. let me just--

1219
01:19:29.236 --> 01:19:30.331
- 'What are we doing?'
- 'Please.'

1220
01:19:30.467 --> 01:19:32.031
Don't shoot him again.

1221
01:19:32.167 --> 01:19:34.967
Okay? Just..

1222
01:19:35.103 --> 01:19:35.970
Just..

1223
01:19:37.980 --> 01:19:39.648
General. thi-this isn't
the first time

1224
01:19:39.783 --> 01:19:41.046
we've had this
conversation. okay?

1225
01:19:41.182 --> 01:19:45.549
That's-that's...because
you're stubborn.

1226
01:19:45.685 --> 01:19:48.052
You won't believe me when I tell
you that Dr. Carter was right.

1227
01:19:48.187 --> 01:19:51.118
That the enemy
can manipulate time.

1228
01:19:51.253 --> 01:19:52.552
The invasion will fail

1229
01:19:52.688 --> 01:19:55.325
no matter how many bodies
you throw at it.

1230
01:19:55.460 --> 01:19:56.996
'The only way to win this war'

1231
01:19:57.132 --> 01:19:59.197
'is by finding
this power source'

1232
01:19:59.332 --> 01:20:00.993
'of the mimic horde
and killing it.'

1233
01:20:01.128 --> 01:20:05.072
And the only means of finding it
is in that safe right there.

1234
01:20:06.936 --> 01:20:09.371
No matter how many times
we have this conversation

1235
01:20:09.507 --> 01:20:11.242
you refuse to accept
that the enemy

1236
01:20:11.378 --> 01:20:14.009
breaks through to London
tomorrow and we lose.

1237
01:20:14.145 --> 01:20:16.045
We lose everything.

1238
01:20:23.155 --> 01:20:25.960
Let's say for one moment..

1239
01:20:26.095 --> 01:20:29.193
...that I can't
rationally explain..

1240
01:20:29.329 --> 01:20:31.157
...your impressive
parlor tricks.

1241
01:20:33.835 --> 01:20:36.201
Dr. Carter told me..

1242
01:20:36.337 --> 01:20:38.364
...this device requires
a live mimic to work.

1243
01:20:38.499 --> 01:20:40.667
What use is it to you?

1244
01:20:40.803 --> 01:20:43.177
- That's my concern.
- On the contrary.

1245
01:20:43.312 --> 01:20:45.746
According to you.
this concerns the whole world.

1246
01:20:45.882 --> 01:20:47.179
Well. what would you do if you

1247
01:20:47.314 --> 01:20:50.411
believed everything
I just told you?

1248
01:20:50.546 --> 01:20:52.312
- I would locate this..
- Omega.

1249
01:20:52.448 --> 01:20:53.890
And bomb it out of existence.

1250
01:20:54.025 --> 01:20:55.986
You're not mentally equipped
to fight this thing.

1251
01:20:56.121 --> 01:20:57.586
And you never will be.

1252
01:21:14.578 --> 01:21:17.076
What do we do now?

1253
01:21:17.212 --> 01:21:19.876
I don't know.
We've never gotten this far.

1254
01:21:26.217 --> 01:21:27.616
- That was easy.
- Now!

1255
01:21:27.751 --> 01:21:29.589
Stop right there! Don't move!

1256
01:21:29.724 --> 01:21:31.224
Nobody move!

1257
01:21:32.760 --> 01:21:33.659
'Weapon!'

1258
01:21:35.194 --> 01:21:36.596
'Stop!'

1259
01:21:40.231 --> 01:21:42.166
They're off and away!

1260
01:21:42.301 --> 01:21:43.231
What am I supposed to do
with this?

1261
01:21:43.366 --> 01:21:45.098
Stick it in your leg.

1262
01:21:45.233 --> 01:21:46.507
Do it!

1263
01:22:04.423 --> 01:22:06.792
<i>Cage. what's happening?</i>

1264
01:22:06.927 --> 01:22:08.259
<i>Talk to me.</i>

1265
01:22:08.394 --> 01:22:09.622
<i>I feel it. it's takin..</i>

1266
01:22:09.757 --> 01:22:11.757
<i>...it's taking me there. umm..</i>

1267
01:22:11.892 --> 01:22:12.859
<i>What do you see?</i>

1268
01:22:14.896 --> 01:22:16.367
<i>It's-it's the Louvre.</i>

1269
01:22:16.502 --> 01:22:18.073
<i>Where? Where are you?</i>

1270
01:22:18.209 --> 01:22:21.505
<i>I'm inside now. It's flooded.</i>

1271
01:22:21.641 --> 01:22:22.909
<i>I'm going down. I'm.</i>
<i>I'm in a garage.</i>

1272
01:22:23.044 --> 01:22:24.937
<i>A garage underneath the museum.</i>

1273
01:22:25.072 --> 01:22:26.646
<i>The Omega. Can you see it?</i>

1274
01:22:33.382 --> 01:22:34.914
It's in Paris.

1275
01:22:52.300 --> 01:22:53.273
Rita!

1276
01:23:00.952 --> 01:23:02.441
'Turn your head!'

1277
01:23:02.576 --> 01:23:04.820
'Stay in the car!'

1278
01:23:04.956 --> 01:23:07.287
'Move away from the car!
Move away!'

1279
01:23:34.851 --> 01:23:37.014
What have you done?

1280
01:23:37.150 --> 01:23:38.516
What have you done?

1281
01:23:40.849 --> 01:23:43.454
You'll be fine.
You just needed blood.

1282
01:23:43.589 --> 01:23:45.951
You don't know
what you've just done.

1283
01:23:46.086 --> 01:23:47.387
I'm not allowed to talk to you.

1284
01:23:47.523 --> 01:23:48.856
I was with someone.

1285
01:23:50.692 --> 01:23:53.128
Rita Vrataski. Is she alive?

1286
01:23:53.264 --> 01:23:54.964
Rita Vrataski.

1287
01:23:55.100 --> 01:23:56.072
Please.

1288
01:23:57.037 --> 01:23:58.305
Just tell me that.

1289
01:24:00.909 --> 01:24:02.874
Please tell me.

1290
01:24:03.009 --> 01:24:03.937
I'm sorry.

1291
01:24:41.376 --> 01:24:43.378
I was out of those things
in three minutes flat. Cage.

1292
01:24:43.513 --> 01:24:44.782
What's wrong with you?

1293
01:24:46.351 --> 01:24:48.390
I thought you were dead.

1294
01:24:48.526 --> 01:24:50.315
Not yet.

1295
01:24:54.691 --> 01:24:55.831
- Sorry. cage.
- No! Whoa-whoa.

1296
01:24:55.967 --> 01:24:58.557
Wait! Wait! I'm out. I'm out.

1297
01:24:58.692 --> 01:25:00.395
They gave me blood.

1298
01:25:04.239 --> 01:25:05.438
'I lost the power.'

1299
01:25:07.645 --> 01:25:09.504
I feel it.

1300
01:25:09.640 --> 01:25:11.246
I can't reset the day anymore.

1301
01:25:26.821 --> 01:25:28.325
We have to kill the Omega

1302
01:25:28.460 --> 01:25:29.825
before the invasion starts.

1303
01:25:31.268 --> 01:25:33.894
That gives us
less than three hours.

1304
01:25:34.029 --> 01:25:36.238
We need a drop ship
to get to Paris in time.

1305
01:25:37.601 --> 01:25:39.537
Need more soldiers too.

1306
01:25:39.672 --> 01:25:41.705
Now who's crazy enough
to follow us to Paris?

1307
01:25:48.949 --> 01:25:50.049
Cage!

1308
01:25:50.185 --> 01:25:51.417
- Cage!
- 'Guys!'

1309
01:25:51.553 --> 01:25:52.851
We've been lookin'
everywhere for you.

1310
01:25:52.987 --> 01:25:54.155
Just listen.

1311
01:25:54.291 --> 01:25:55.647
Farell almost strung us up
by our bollocks

1312
01:25:55.783 --> 01:25:56.889
for losing track of you!

1313
01:25:57.024 --> 01:25:58.389
Just listen.

1314
01:25:58.525 --> 01:26:00.161
You're gonna wanna hear
this story.

1315
01:26:00.297 --> 01:26:01.560
Now. it's gonna sound ridiculous
at first

1316
01:26:01.695 --> 01:26:03.392
but the longer I talk
the more rational

1317
01:26:03.527 --> 01:26:04.598
it's going to appear.

1318
01:26:04.734 --> 01:26:05.659
Yeah?

1319
01:26:05.795 --> 01:26:07.994
He named the school I went to.

1320
01:26:08.129 --> 01:26:10.706
And then he tells me
my second grade teacher

1321
01:26:10.841 --> 01:26:11.931
was called Miss Polio.

1322
01:26:12.067 --> 01:26:13.203
She wouldn't let him go
to the bathroom

1323
01:26:13.339 --> 01:26:15.103
made him wet his pants.

1324
01:26:15.239 --> 01:26:16.878
Shut up!

1325
01:26:17.014 --> 01:26:18.873
Look. I am telling you. man.

1326
01:26:19.008 --> 01:26:22.016
He knows everything
about all of us.

1327
01:26:22.151 --> 01:26:24.681
- Bullshit.
- Yeah?

1328
01:26:24.816 --> 01:26:27.812
He says your name
ain't really Ford.

1329
01:26:27.948 --> 01:26:29.518
Says Ford was your friend.

1330
01:26:29.653 --> 01:26:31.755
Died in combat on his first day.

1331
01:26:31.891 --> 01:26:34.554
'You took his place.
Send your checks to his family.'

1332
01:26:34.690 --> 01:26:37.092
You slippery bitch.

1333
01:26:37.227 --> 01:26:38.991
'Cage says the enemy
knows us too.'

1334
01:26:39.126 --> 01:26:40.765
'They're waitin' for us
on the beach.'

1335
01:26:40.901 --> 01:26:44.267
And we all die. the whole
invasion is a slaughter.

1336
01:26:44.403 --> 01:26:46.431
Well. this is great.

1337
01:26:46.567 --> 01:26:48.701
Really good confidence boost
for tomorrow. Thanks. Cage.

1338
01:26:48.837 --> 01:26:50.676
But we can change it. right?

1339
01:26:50.812 --> 01:26:52.510
I mean. there has to be
somethin' that we can do.

1340
01:26:52.646 --> 01:26:55.009
There has to be...a way
that we can win.

1341
01:26:56.480 --> 01:26:58.214
There is a chance.

1342
01:26:58.349 --> 01:27:00.585
It's a slim one.

1343
01:27:00.721 --> 01:27:03.587
But it means coming
with me right now.

1344
01:27:03.723 --> 01:27:05.456
Listen. pal. I don't really care

1345
01:27:05.591 --> 01:27:07.928
what you think you know
about us.

1346
01:27:08.063 --> 01:27:10.760
'We just met you.'

1347
01:27:10.896 --> 01:27:13.066
Come on. why would we
follow him into combat?

1348
01:27:18.240 --> 01:27:20.470
I don't expect you to follow me.

1349
01:27:20.605 --> 01:27:22.036
I expect you to follow her.

1350
01:27:26.711 --> 01:27:28.284
That's the full metal J-squad.

1351
01:27:29.910 --> 01:27:32.012
This is Rita Vrataski.

1352
01:27:32.147 --> 01:27:34.680
- Otherwise known as--
- Yeah. yeah.

1353
01:27:34.816 --> 01:27:37.287
The Angel of Verdun.

1354
01:27:47.298 --> 01:27:48.836
Okay.

1355
01:27:57.742 --> 01:27:59.605
It's a new day. people.

1356
01:27:59.741 --> 01:28:01.208
Destiny calls.

1357
01:28:01.344 --> 01:28:04.781
The world expects only one thing
from us. that we will win.

1358
01:28:04.916 --> 01:28:06.551
Rest assured the enemy
will thank you

1359
01:28:06.686 --> 01:28:08.690
for not giving
a hundred percent today.

1360
01:28:08.825 --> 01:28:09.787
Squad.

1361
01:28:13.259 --> 01:28:14.522
Where's J squad?

1362
01:28:32.946 --> 01:28:35.978
Right. okay. so this Omega.
it controls time.

1363
01:28:36.113 --> 01:28:37.484
Just blow the new age
piece of bollocks

1364
01:28:37.619 --> 01:28:40.486
back where it came from.
and then we go home.

1365
01:28:40.622 --> 01:28:42.187
Right. it-it's guarded
by an alpha.

1366
01:28:42.323 --> 01:28:44.389
Just kill it. Okay?

1367
01:28:44.525 --> 01:28:46.687
No. you heard what Cage said.

1368
01:28:46.822 --> 01:28:48.525
Do not kill an Alpha.

1369
01:28:48.661 --> 01:28:49.690
If we kill an alpha. the Omega

1370
01:28:49.826 --> 01:28:51.963
will reset this whole day.

1371
01:28:52.098 --> 01:28:53.863
We'll never even remember
we had this conversation.

1372
01:28:53.998 --> 01:28:55.037
And they're gonna know
we're coming.

1373
01:28:55.172 --> 01:28:56.169
So what am I supposed to do

1374
01:28:56.304 --> 01:28:57.301
if one of those alphas

1375
01:28:57.436 --> 01:28:58.469
is about to kill me?

1376
01:28:58.604 --> 01:29:00.002
You take a hit for the team.

1377
01:29:03.707 --> 01:29:05.246
When we're on the ground

1378
01:29:05.381 --> 01:29:06.410
there's not gonna be
a lot of time

1379
01:29:06.546 --> 01:29:07.977
before they know we're there.

1380
01:29:09.516 --> 01:29:10.980
We're gonna need eyes up here.

1381
01:29:12.815 --> 01:29:14.086
I'm going in. Cage.

1382
01:29:25.664 --> 01:29:27.194
Thirty seconds till contact.

1383
01:29:42.176 --> 01:29:44.083
- Cage!
- Oh. no! Oh!

1384
01:29:44.218 --> 01:29:45.487
Kimmel! Now!

1385
01:29:54.426 --> 01:29:56.087
Ford! Let's go!

1386
01:29:56.223 --> 01:29:57.728
- Cage!
- Drop. Nance!

1387
01:29:57.864 --> 01:29:59.231
Talk to him. Rita! We gotta go.

1388
01:29:59.366 --> 01:30:00.431
- Drop.
- Cage..

1389
01:30:00.567 --> 01:30:02.102
They know we're coming. man!

1390
01:30:02.237 --> 01:30:05.441
Drop! Drop! Drop!

1391
01:30:07.267 --> 01:30:09.139
- Drop.
- You're not hooked in.

1392
01:32:27.548 --> 01:32:28.815
What took you so long?

1393
01:32:31.847 --> 01:32:32.918
Any others?

1394
01:32:38.056 --> 01:32:39.226
'We're low on ammo.'

1395
01:32:39.362 --> 01:32:40.656
'I've got one Claymore.'

1396
01:32:40.792 --> 01:32:42.256
'Ford. you're out.'

1397
01:32:42.392 --> 01:32:44.055
Griff has only got
half a magazine left

1398
01:32:44.191 --> 01:32:45.356
and he can hardly move.

1399
01:32:45.492 --> 01:32:47.125
'I thought you could see
the future.'

1400
01:32:47.261 --> 01:32:49.702
I haven't lived this day.

1401
01:32:49.838 --> 01:32:51.406
I don't know
what's gonna happen.

1402
01:32:51.541 --> 01:32:53.440
It doesn't matter.

1403
01:32:53.575 --> 01:32:55.738
What matters is we finish this.

1404
01:32:55.874 --> 01:32:57.873
With what?

1405
01:32:58.008 --> 01:32:59.776
'I mean. Griff can't even walk.'

1406
01:32:59.911 --> 01:33:01.481
'We're three men down. Come on.'

1407
01:33:01.616 --> 01:33:02.711
Look. We're running out of time.

1408
01:33:02.846 --> 01:33:04.412
Collect your ammo.

1409
01:33:04.548 --> 01:33:05.716
'There must be
a thousand mimics'

1410
01:33:05.851 --> 01:33:07.283
between us and that pyramid.

1411
01:33:07.418 --> 01:33:09.284
So. what we gonna do.
just walk up to the front door?

1412
01:33:09.419 --> 01:33:11.218
- 'Is that it?'
- If we stay here. we die.

1413
01:33:11.354 --> 01:33:14.161
'Yeah? We'll never get through.'

1414
01:33:14.296 --> 01:33:15.257
We could..

1415
01:33:17.596 --> 01:33:18.557
...in that.

1416
01:33:20.370 --> 01:33:22.830
That ship will never fly.

1417
01:33:22.966 --> 01:33:24.970
Doesn't need to fly.

1418
01:33:25.105 --> 01:33:28.805
It just needs to get us
across there with speed.

1419
01:33:28.940 --> 01:33:30.943
If the engines are still running

1420
01:33:31.078 --> 01:33:32.846
we could steer it
with the power levers.

1421
01:33:34.109 --> 01:33:36.652
Skinner...clear a path.

1422
01:33:42.452 --> 01:33:44.149
- 'Try it again. now.'
- No. it's not reading.

1423
01:33:44.284 --> 01:33:45.661
Condition lever. low.

1424
01:33:52.492 --> 01:33:54.199
'Master power. on.'

1425
01:33:57.107 --> 01:33:59.163
Griff!

1426
01:33:59.299 --> 01:34:00.973
We've gotta go! Come on!

1427
01:34:04.037 --> 01:34:07.007
I'm not gonna be any good
in there. mate.

1428
01:34:07.142 --> 01:34:08.545
Let me buy you some time.

1429
01:34:13.787 --> 01:34:15.586
Power's on.

1430
01:34:15.722 --> 01:34:16.923
This is gonna work.

1431
01:34:17.555 --> 01:34:19.055
Hey!

1432
01:34:19.190 --> 01:34:21.427
Hey. come on. man!
We gotta go!

1433
01:34:21.562 --> 01:34:23.030
Don't wait for us!

1434
01:34:23.166 --> 01:34:24.331
Skinner!

1435
01:34:24.466 --> 01:34:26.557
'Griff. come on!'

1436
01:34:26.693 --> 01:34:27.830
We're good to go.
Where are they?

1437
01:34:27.965 --> 01:34:29.732
Where's Skinner and Griff?

1438
01:34:29.868 --> 01:34:31.003
They're not comin'.

1439
01:34:44.546 --> 01:34:46.315
Go. brother. You gotta go. man.

1440
01:34:47.690 --> 01:34:49.219
I'll see you
in the next life.

1441
01:34:54.561 --> 01:34:55.988
Bollocks.

1442
01:34:57.896 --> 01:34:59.429
Move over! Move over!

1443
01:35:01.832 --> 01:35:03.030
We gotta go!

1444
01:35:03.165 --> 01:35:05.769
Yo. we gotta go. Now!

1445
01:35:08.401 --> 01:35:10.011
They're coming. Cage.

1446
01:35:16.345 --> 01:35:19.020
- Aah!
- Come on. you bastards!

1447
01:35:19.156 --> 01:35:20.347
Come on!

1448
01:35:20.482 --> 01:35:21.883
'Reload.'

1449
01:35:22.018 --> 01:35:24.683
'Reload. Reload.'

1450
01:35:36.504 --> 01:35:37.905
We got incoming!

1451
01:35:46.415 --> 01:35:48.513
Ah. come on!

1452
01:35:56.316 --> 01:35:57.287
'Cage!'

1453
01:36:08.768 --> 01:36:10.135
You have to take over!

1454
01:36:50.643 --> 01:36:51.673
No!

1455
01:37:03.326 --> 01:37:06.317
Rita!

1456
01:37:06.453 --> 01:37:07.856
Punch it! Punch it!

1457
01:37:46.065 --> 01:37:47.265
We've been through worse.

1458
01:38:26.805 --> 01:38:27.767
Okay.

1459
01:38:29.779 --> 01:38:30.737
'It's there.'

1460
01:38:32.209 --> 01:38:33.245
In the water. There.

1461
01:39:01.104 --> 01:39:02.270
That's an Alpha.

1462
01:39:02.405 --> 01:39:05.112
I'm gonna draw that thing away.

1463
01:39:06.275 --> 01:39:07.677
You kill the Omega.

1464
01:39:07.813 --> 01:39:08.847
No.

1465
01:39:08.983 --> 01:39:10.148
You won't make it 10 feet

1466
01:39:10.284 --> 01:39:12.414
before that thing
kills you. Cage.

1467
01:39:12.550 --> 01:39:14.084
- I can do it.
- Take the grenades.

1468
01:39:14.220 --> 01:39:17.117
- I can do it.
- Listen to me.

1469
01:39:17.252 --> 01:39:18.851
Listen to me.

1470
01:39:18.986 --> 01:39:21.188
Neither one of us
is getting out of here.

1471
01:39:44.780 --> 01:39:48.551
Thank you...for getting me
this far.

1472
01:39:54.027 --> 01:39:55.492
You're a good man. Cage.

1473
01:39:57.663 --> 01:39:59.731
I wish I had the chance
to know you better.

1474
01:43:30.211 --> 01:43:31.870
Welcome to London. Major.

1475
01:43:32.006 --> 01:43:33.872
I'm Corporal Montgomery
your liaison

1476
01:43:34.007 --> 01:43:35.745
to General Brigham's
press office.

1477
01:43:36.644 --> 01:43:37.945
Very good to have you.

1478
01:43:39.553 --> 01:43:41.553
Have you heard the news?
Isn't it brilliant.

1479
01:43:49.996 --> 01:43:52.398
Just before sunrise
this morning

1480
01:43:52.534 --> 01:43:55.699
a large surge of energy
was detected in Paris.

1481
01:43:55.834 --> 01:43:59.307
We do not know exactly
what this signifies

1482
01:43:59.442 --> 01:44:01.933
'but the result appears
to be a total collapse'

1483
01:44:02.068 --> 01:44:03.905
of the enemy's capacity
to fight.

1484
01:44:05.275 --> 01:44:08.442
Russian and Chinese troops
are now moving across Europe

1485
01:44:08.578 --> 01:44:11.077
without resistance.

1486
01:44:11.213 --> 01:44:14.147
'Tomorrow. we advance
on the western front.'

1487
01:44:14.282 --> 01:44:16.615
'We believe we are marching
to claim a victory'

1488
01:44:16.750 --> 01:44:18.486
'for ourselves..'

1489
01:44:18.621 --> 01:44:20.092
<i>for our loved ones</i>

1490
01:44:20.227 --> 01:44:21.754
<i>for our countrymen</i>

1491
01:44:21.890 --> 01:44:23.692
<i>for the entire human race.</i>

1492
01:44:23.828 --> 01:44:25.266
What are you?! Sound off!

1493
01:44:25.402 --> 01:44:27.432
- I'm a warrior!
- What do warriors do?

1494
01:44:27.567 --> 01:44:29.633
- Kill! Kill!
- What are you gonna do?

1495
01:44:29.768 --> 01:44:31.038
You have not been
in twenty battles.

1496
01:44:31.174 --> 01:44:32.438
- Ford.
- I have too.

1497
01:44:32.574 --> 01:44:33.702
You're gonna dump your load
the second

1498
01:44:33.838 --> 01:44:35.034
you hit the beach tomorrow.
Ford.

1499
01:44:35.169 --> 01:44:36.376
How about you two
go get yourselves

1500
01:44:36.511 --> 01:44:38.477
a nice hot cup of
shut-the-hell-up!

1501
01:44:38.612 --> 01:44:40.444
You funny. girl.
but I bet you

1502
01:44:40.579 --> 01:44:42.215
I set some kind of
record tomorrow.

1503
01:44:42.351 --> 01:44:44.182
Fastest time runnin' backwards.
Ford

1504
01:44:44.318 --> 01:44:46.220
slippin' in your own shit.

1505
01:44:46.356 --> 01:44:47.718
'Knock off the grab-ass!'

1506
01:44:49.592 --> 01:44:51.884
- 'What are you?! Sound off!'
- I'm a warrior!

1507
01:44:52.019 --> 01:44:53.988
- 'What do warriors do?'
- Kill!

1508
01:44:56.591 --> 01:44:57.860
Attention!

1509
01:45:37.873 --> 01:45:38.835
Yes?

1510
01:45:39.965 --> 01:45:41.068
What do you want?

1510
01:45:42.305 --> 01:46:42.394
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm
